@Node "NODE_CGXMODE_EDITWND_REAL_KEYS" "CyberGraphX4.guide/NODE_CGXMODE_EDITWND_REAL_KEYS"
@Prev "NODE_CGXMODE_EDITWND_REAL"
@Next "NODE_CGXMODE_EDITWND_NAME"
@Toc "NODE_CGXMODE_EDITWND_REAL"
@{CODE}

	@{u}TestMode edit window keyboard shortcuts@{uu}

		Here is a overview table for the available keyboard shortcuts
	on the testmode screen:

	@{i}ESC @{ui}
		Will exit the Test-Edit Mode and restore the values if you had
	changed any while editing on the test pattern screen

	@{i}RETURN @{ui}
		Will accept the values you have edited and take you back to
	the Edit Mode window and update the new number there

	@{i}i @{ui}
		Will inverse all the colors on the test pattern screen, ie black to
	white etc...

	@{i}x @{ui}
		Will set the pixelclock [Hz] to it's real value

	@{i}+ @{ui}
		Increases the pixelclock in steps of 10000Hz

	@{i}- @{ui}
		Decreases the pixelclock in steps of 10000Hz

	@{i}[UP-ARROW] @{ui}
		This is used for centering the screen by moving the screen
	up. This key edits the Vertical Pulse Offset (It adds milliseconds
        (ms) to the current value).

	@{i}[DOWN-ARROW] @{ui}
		This is used for centering the screen by moving the
	screen down. This key edits the Vertical Pulse Offset (It subtracts
	milliseconds (ms) from the current value).

	@{i}[LEFT-ARROW] @{ui}
		This is used for centering the screen by moving the
	screen left. This key edits the Horizontal Pulse Offset (It adds
	microseconds (탎) to the current value).

	@{i}[RIGHT-ARROW] @{ui}
		This is used for centering the screen by moving the screen 
	right. This key edits the Horizontal Pulse Offset (It subtracts 
	microseconds (탎) from the current value).

	@{i}[SHIFT]+[UP-ARROW] @{ui}
		This is used for making the vertical height (tallness) of the
	screen bigger. This key edits the Vertical Sync Lenght (It subtracts 
	milliseconds (ms) from the current value).

	@{i}[SHIFT]+[DOWN-ARROW] @{ui}
		This is used for making the vertical height (tallness) of the
	screen smaller. This key edits the Vertical Sync Lenght (It adds 
	milliseconds (ms) to the current value).

	@{i}[SHIFT]+[LEFT-ARROW] @{ui}
		This is used for making the horizontal width (wideness) of the
	screen bigger. This key edits the Horizontal Sync Lenght (It subtracts
	milliseconds (ms) from the current value).

	@{i}[SHIFT]+[RIGHT-ARROW] @{ui}
		This is used for making the horizontal width (wideness) of the
	screen smaller. This key edits the Horizontal Sync Lenght (It adds 
	milliseconds (ms) to the current value).

@EndNode

