@{CODE}

	@{u}Monitor Specification@{uu}

		This is where you can tell CGXMode the display specifications for your monitor.
	The manual for your monitor should have most of these numbers in the back. If it
	does not then you should contact the MFG of your monitor (or check their web
	site) to get the correct numbers. The more numbers you can feed into the Monitor
	Specification settings the more you can get out of your monitor with CGX. If you
	plug a few numbers in and guess others it _will_ be a pain to edit screen modes
	and you will not get the results you need or want. MAKE SURE you input the
	correct numbers, if you guess and you are wrong you might damage your monitor:
	You will see this everytime you edit your monitors specification:

	In this window you can enter all of your monitors display specifications


	@{b}Gadgets @{ub}

	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_MONLIST"} Defaults
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_NAME"} Monitor name
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_BANDWIDTH"} Monitor Bandwidth
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_HFREQMIN"} Min. Horizontal Frequency
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_HFREQMAX"} Max. Horizontal Frequency
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_HSYNCMINTIME"} Min Time Horizontal Sync
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_HSYNCMINPULSE"} Min Pulse Horizontal Sync
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_VFREQMIN"} Min. Vertical Frequency
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_VFREQMAX"} Max. Vertical Frequency
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_VSYNCMINTIME"} Min Time Vertical Sync
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_VSYNCMINPULSE"} Min Pulse Vertical Sync
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_Use"} Use
	@{"    " Link "NODE_CGXMODE_MONWND_Cancel"} Cancel


